CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper,r October 11, 1952, pg. 16 reads: "Visiting Ministers At AME Conference - An unusual number of visiting ministers and laymen attended the Pittsburgh Annual Conference held last week in Bethel AME Church. Reading left to right, front row; the Revs. G.W. Patterson, J.A. Whitfield, R.H. Reed Jr., C.S. Spivey Sr., Bishop A.J. Allen, who posed with his brethren; N.W. Burton, H.L. Anderson, A.C. Brogdon and Norman W. Browne.  Back row, left to right: The Revs. J.S. Harris, J.D. Jenkins, D.G. Jacobs, W.S.T. Jordon, F.W. Thompson, C.E. Drummer and A.S. King.  Rear: E.W. Jackson and J.C. Burton. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, front row from left: Rev. G. W. Patterson, Rev. J. A. Whitfield, Rev. R. H. Reed Jr., Rev. C. S. Spivey Sr., Bishop A. J. Allen, Rev. N. W. Burton, Rev. H. L. Anderson, Rev. A. C. Brogdon, Norman W. Browne; second row: Rev. J. S. Harris, Rev. J. D. Jenkins, Rev. D. G. Jacobs, Rev. W. S. T. Jordon, Rev. F. W. Thompson, Rev. C. E. Drummer, Rev. A. S. King; rear: Rev. E. W. Jackson, and Rev. J. C. Burton, posed in Bethel AME Church for conference
